CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 22, 1958, p. 19, reads: "JAZZ BASH - Ahmad Jamal, whose album, "But Not for Me," currently leads the nation's music charts, and Walt Harper's combo, breaking it up on the local college circuit, were featured together, recently, ast a cabaret sponsored by the Pittsburgh Modern Jazz Society at the Copa. Left to right: Harper, Jamal with trio members, Israel Crosby and Vernel Forneir. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Walt Harper shaking hands with Ahmad Jamal, next to Jamal's trio members Israel Crosby, and Vernel Fornier, in Copa Club for cabaret sponsored by Pittsburgh Modern Jazz Society
